14 §4084. Purchase of supplies; machinery and equipment; emergency purchase;
15 preference to home merchants
16 A.(1)(a) All purchases of materials or supplies required by the board for the
17 conduct, operation, maintenance, and repair of the public systems of sewerage,
18 water, and drainage exceeding the sum of thirty thousand dollars shall be advertised
19 and let by contract to the lowest responsible bidder who has bid according to the
20 contract plans and specifications as advertised shall be made in accordance with the
21 provisions of R.S. 38:2212.1(A)(1)(a).
22 (b) However, purchases of ten thousand dollars or more, but not more than
23 thirty thousand dollars, shall be made by obtaining not less than three quotes by
24 telephone, facsimile, email, or any other electronic form. If telephone quotes are
25 received, a written confirmation of the accepted offers shall be obtained and made
26 a part of the purchase file. If quotations lower than the accepted quotation are
